<subSubSection id="90E3652CFFC7FF83FF090871FBA8A7E5" pageId="10" pageNumber="259" type="description">
<paragraph id="D84636A7FFC7FF83FF090871FCF1A603" blockId="10.[140,1108,236,897]" pageId="10" pageNumber="259">
This widely distributed Holarctic species was formerly known in North America as 
<taxonomicName id="1FF94D24FFC7FF83FF3C085CFD1AA5F0" authority="Crotch, 1873" authorityName="Crotch" authorityYear="1873" box="[140,643,378,404]" class="Insecta" family="Haliplidae" genus="Haliplus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="259" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="subguttatus" subGenus="Liaphlus">
<emphasis id="EA8DEAB5FFC7FF83FF3C085CFE7BA5F0" box="[140,482,378,404]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="259">Haliplus (Liaphlus) subguttatus</emphasis>
Crotch, 1873
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="1FF94D24FFC7FF83FD0C085CFB99A5F0" authorityName="Wallis" authorityYear="1933" box="[700,1024,378,404]" class="Insecta" family="Haliplidae" genus="Haliplus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="259" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="salinarius" subGenus="Liaphlus">
<emphasis id="EA8DEAB5FFC7FF83FD0C085CFB99A5F0" box="[700,1024,378,404]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="259">Haliplus (Liaphlus) salinarius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<bibRefCitation id="BC684B56FFC7FF83FBB7085CFF50A5D3" author="Wallis JB" pageId="10" pageNumber="259" pagination="1 - 76" refId="ref7379" refString="Wallis JB (1933) Revision of the North American species (north of Mexico) of the genus Haliplus Latreille. Transactions of the Royal Canadian Institute 19 (1): 1 - 76." type="journal article" year="1933">
<collectingCountry id="A0EE7637FFC7FF83FBB7085CFBD6A5F0" box="[1031,1103,378,404]" name="United Kingdom" pageId="10" pageNumber="259">Wallis</collectingCountry>
, 1933
</bibRefCitation>
, two names that were synonymized by 
<bibRefCitation id="BC684B56FFC7FF83FD3108BBFCB3A5D3" author="Vondel BJ van" box="[641,810,413,439]" pageId="10" pageNumber="259" pagination="75 - 144" refId="ref7220" refString="Vondel BJ van (1991) Revision of the Palaearctic species of Haliplus subgenus Liaphlus Guignot (Coleoptera: Haliplidae). Tijdschrift voor Entomologie 134: 75 - 144." type="journal article" year="1991">Vondel (1991)</bibRefCitation>
. 
<bibRefCitation id="BC684B56FFC7FF83FC8508BBFC72A5DC" author="Brigham WU" box="[821,1003,413,440]" pageId="10" pageNumber="259" refId="ref6480" refString="Brigham WU (1996) Haliplidae: Checklist of genera. http: // www. inhs. uiuc. edu / biod / waterbeetles / haliplidae / genera. html [accessed 5 January 2009]" type="url" year="1996">Brigham (1996)</bibRefCitation>
accepted the synonymy of 
<taxonomicName id="1FF94D24FFC7FF83FEFF08E7FE2AA5BE" baseAuthorityName="Fabricius" baseAuthorityYear="1801" box="[335,435,448,474]" class="Insecta" family="Haliplidae" genus="Haliplus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="259" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fulvus">
<emphasis id="EA8DEAB5FFC7FF83FEFF08E7FE2AA5BE" box="[335,435,448,474]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="259">H. fulvus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="1FF94D24FFC7FF83FE5B08E7FDE1A5BE" authorityName="Wallis" authorityYear="1933" box="[491,632,448,474]" class="Insecta" family="Haliplidae" genus="Haliplus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="259" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="salinarius">
<emphasis id="EA8DEAB5FFC7FF83FE5B08E7FDE1A5BE" box="[491,632,448,474]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="259">H. salinarius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but disagreed about 
<taxonomicName id="1FF94D24FFC7FF83FCDB08E7FB90A5BE" authorityName="Crotch" authorityYear="1873" box="[875,1033,448,474]" class="Insecta" family="Haliplidae" genus="Haliplus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="259" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="subguttatus">
<emphasis id="EA8DEAB5FFC7FF83FCDB08E7FB90A5BE" box="[875,1033,448,474]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="259">H. subguttatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Since 1991, long series of both Nearctic species have been examined by BJV, but no reliable characters have been found to distinguish the two species and the shape of the aedeagus of 
<taxonomicName id="1FF94D24FFC7FF83FF190B0DFEDFA620" authorityName="Crotch" authorityYear="1873" box="[169,326,554,580]" class="Insecta" family="Haliplidae" genus="Haliplus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="259" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="subguttatus">
<emphasis id="EA8DEAB5FFC7FF83FF190B0DFEDFA620" box="[169,326,554,580]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="259">H. subguttatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
falls within the range of variation exhibited by specimens of 
<taxonomicName id="1FF94D24FFC7FF83FC580B0DFBD5A620" baseAuthorityName="Fabricius" baseAuthorityYear="1801" box="[1000,1100,554,580]" class="Insecta" family="Haliplidae" genus="Haliplus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="259" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fulvus">
<emphasis id="EA8DEAB5FFC7FF83FC580B0DFBD5A620" box="[1000,1100,554,580]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="259">H. fulvus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Accordingly, the synonymy of 
<bibRefCitation id="BC684B56FFC7FF83FE540B6BFD13A603" author="Vondel BJ van" box="[484,650,589,615]" pageId="10" pageNumber="259" pagination="75 - 144" refId="ref7220" refString="Vondel BJ van (1991) Revision of the Palaearctic species of Haliplus subgenus Liaphlus Guignot (Coleoptera: Haliplidae). Tijdschrift voor Entomologie 134: 75 - 144." type="journal article" year="1991">Vondel (1991)</bibRefCitation>
is maintained here.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D84636A7FFC7FF83FF090B56FBA8A7E5" blockId="10.[140,1108,236,897]" pageId="10" pageNumber="259">
This species was recorded from Nova Scotia by 
<bibRefCitation id="BC684B56FFC7FF83FD780B56FCC6A6EE" author="Wallis JB" box="[712,863,624,650]" pageId="10" pageNumber="259" pagination="1 - 76" refId="ref7379" refString="Wallis JB (1933) Revision of the North American species (north of Mexico) of the genus Haliplus Latreille. Transactions of the Royal Canadian Institute 19 (1): 1 - 76." type="journal article" year="1933">
<collectingCountry id="A0EE7637FFC7FF83FD780B56FC93A6EE" box="[712,778,624,650]" name="United Kingdom" pageId="10" pageNumber="259">Wallis</collectingCountry>
(1933)
</bibRefCitation>
, and then from Newfoundland by 
<bibRefCitation id="BC684B56FFC7FF83FE950BB5FE47A6CA" author="Roughley RE" box="[293,478,659,686]" pageId="10" pageNumber="259" pagination="60 - 61" refId="ref6949" refString="Roughley RE (1991) Family Haliplidae: Crawling Water Beetles. In: Bousquet Y (Ed) Checklist of Beetles of Canada and Alaska. Ottawa, Ontario: Agriculture Canada, publication 1861 / E: 60 - 61. http: // www. canacoll. org / Coleo / Checklist / PDF files / HALIPLIDAE. pdf [accessed 5 January 2009]" type="journal article" year="1991">Roughley (1991)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation id="BC684B56FFC7FF83FDA50BB5FD2AA6CA" author="Vondel BJ van" box="[533,691,659,686]" pageId="10" pageNumber="259" pagination="75 - 144" refId="ref7220" refString="Vondel BJ van (1991) Revision of the Palaearctic species of Haliplus subgenus Liaphlus Guignot (Coleoptera: Haliplidae). Tijdschrift voor Entomologie 134: 75 - 144." type="journal article" year="1991">Vondel (1991)</bibRefCitation>
(Fig. 1). In the Old World it is widely distributed from 
<collectingCountry id="A0EE7637FFC7FF83FEFE0B91FE04A6B5" box="[334,413,695,721]" name="Iceland" pageId="10" pageNumber="259">Iceland</collectingCountry>
throughout Europe, south to North Africa, east through the Middle East, south to 
<collectingCountry id="A0EE7637FFC7FF83FECD0BFCFE32A690" box="[381,427,730,756]" name="Iraq" pageId="10" pageNumber="259">Iraq</collectingCountry>
, and across Central Asia and Siberia as far as Lake Baikal (
<bibRefCitation id="BC684B56FFC7FF83FBAB0BFCFF68A773" author="Vondel BJ van" pageId="10" pageNumber="259" pagination="75 - 144" refId="ref7220" refString="Vondel BJ van (1991) Revision of the Palaearctic species of Haliplus subgenus Liaphlus Guignot (Coleoptera: Haliplidae). Tijdschrift voor Entomologie 134: 75 - 144." type="journal article" year="1991">Vondel 1991</bibRefCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation id="BC684B56FFC7FF83FEB60BDBFE3EA773" author="Vondel BJ van" box="[262,423,765,791]" pageId="10" pageNumber="259" pagination="75 - 144" refId="ref7220" refString="Vondel BJ van (1991) Revision of the Palaearctic species of Haliplus subgenus Liaphlus Guignot (Coleoptera: Haliplidae). Tijdschrift voor Entomologie 134: 75 - 144." type="journal article" year="1991">Vondel (1991)</bibRefCitation>
summarized its biology, indicating that it is found in clear or peaty stagnant or slowly running water, in lakes, pools, canals, rivers, and ditches, and has even been recorded in brackish water. Larvae probably feed on algae such as 
<taxonomicName id="1FF94D24FFC7FF83FC790A65FB88A739" authorityName="C.A.Agardh" authorityYear="1824" box="[969,1041,835,861]" class="Charophyceae" family="Characeae" genus="Nitella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Charales" pageId="10" pageNumber="259" phylum="Charophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="EA8DEAB5FFC7FF83FC790A65FB88A739" box="[969,1041,835,861]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="259">Nitella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
while adults are omnivorous feeding on algae, pollen, and invertebrates such as oligochaetes.
</paragraph>
